  "text": "Let k be an algebraically closed field of characteristic p > 0. An Artin-Schreier k-curve is a smooth projective connected k-curve Y which is a Z/p-cover of the projective line P 1 k . In [CITATION_1] , the authors introduce the moduli space AS g of Artin-Schreier k-curves of genus g. They enumerate a family of irreducible strata of AS g by partitions of the integer d + 2 where d := 2g/(p − 1) such that no entries are congruent to 1 modulo p. From there, Pries and Zhu give the formula to calculate the dimension of a stratum from its corresponding partition (see [CITATION_2] Corollary 3 .11]). Furthermore, they construct a deformation to show whether a stratum lies in the closure of another under certain conditions (see [CITATION_3] Proposition 4 .6]). That technique, combine with the results of Maugeais in [CITATION_4] which showed that each irreducible component of AS g has dimension 2g/(p − 1) − 1, allowed them to determine all the cases when the moduli space of such covers is irreducible (see [PZ12, Corollary 1.2]).",
